<CSSInset-block>
<summary>
The <strong><c>inset-block</c></strong> <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS">CSS</see> property defines the logical block start and end offsets of an element, which maps to physical offsets depending on the element's writing mode, directionality, and text orientation. It corresponds to the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/top">top</see> and <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/bottom">bottom</see>, or <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/right">right</see> and <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/left">left</see> properties depending on the values defined for <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/writing-mode">writing-mode</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/direction">direction</see>, and <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/text-orientation">text-orientation</see>.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>EmbedInteractiveExample("pages/css/inset-block.html")</para>
<para>-The mapped physical properties: <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/top">top</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/right">right</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/bottom">bottom</see>, and <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/left">left</see><br/>-The mapped physical shortcut: <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/inset">inset</see><br/>-The mapped inline shortcut: <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/inset-inline">inset-inline</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/writing-mode">writing-mode</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/direction">direction</see>, <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/text-orientation">text-orientation</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/inset-block"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<value>The <c>inset-block</c> property takes the same values as the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/left">left</see> property.</value>
</CSSInset-block>
